The evidence with the title 'Tackling the "vocabulary gap" between Rich And Poor Children ... ' says Feb 16, 2014  ... By age three , children from lower income families may hear up to 30 million fewer words than their more affluent peers .  ... According to Fernald , five-year-old children of lower socioeconomic status ( SES ) score two years behind on standardized language development tests by the time they enter school. 
